# Global Mentions

## Context
The application requires a robust mention system across all inputs (comments, threads, global chat, inbox). Users need the ability to mention specific users (`@user`), roles (`@role`), `@here`, and `@everyone`. These mentions must render inline as rich badges globally.

## Goal
- Enhance TipTap editor to support mentions (`@user`, `@role`, `@here`, `@everyone`).
- Implement text rendering and rich input reconciliation to parse mentions from raw text or rich text and render them as inline badges.
- Mentioning a role/group should notify all members of that role.
- Support site-wide application of this feature (forum, chat, inbox).

## Non-Goals
- Real-time pop-up notifications for mentions (out of scope if not specified, focus on text rendering and badge reconciliation first).

## Steps
1. **TipTap Extension**: Configure/extend TipTap's mention extension to query users, roles, `here`, and `everyone` from the backend.
2. **Backend Parsing/Notification**: When an entity containing mentions is saved, the backend needs to parse mentions, resolve them to specific user IDs, and dispatch notification events.
3. **Frontend Rendering**: Implement a global text renderer or sanitization wrapper that identifies mention formats (e.g. `<span data-type="mention" data-id="...">@username</span>` or regex `@[a-zA-Z0-9_]+`) and transforms them into rich inline badges (React components).
4. **Integration**: Apply the renderer to Thread viewer, Comments, Inbox, and Global Chat.

## Verification
- Typing `@` opens a suggestion list with users and roles.
- Mentioning `@everyone` notifies all users.
- Mentions render as highlighted badges in read-only views across the site.

